:{{DIcon|?}} Do you need to retrieve any books?
::<!--Trigger PerformanceD 404025001: Config/Level/Mission/4040250/Act/Act404025001.json-->
:;(If {{cx}}<!--SubMission Finish: 202020104-->)
:::'''Yuluo:''' Oh, aren't you the one who asked for the ''Compendium of Remedies'' last time? I helped you last time, so could you do me a favor in return?
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_414250007-->
:;(If {{cx}}<!--SubMission not Finish: 202020104-->)
:::'''Yuluo:''' ...Well, some books have gone missing from the Alchemy Commission, and, well, they're essentially some very troublesome texts. That, and Lady Dan Shu hasn't left me any clues. How am I supposed to get them back?...
:::'''Yuluo:''' ...Ah, I forgot again. I shouldn't call her "Lady" now. So, what brings you here?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is there anything I can help with?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414250007-->
::'''Yuluo:''' Please forgive me for this awkward situation. Actually, in addition to medical texts, we also keep some "forbidden tomes" here in the Alchemy Commission. They are supposed to be carefully preserved, but now they've been stolen.
::'''Yuluo:''' I guess the theft has something to do with the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus as well. I've asked the Seat of Divine Foresight, but they haven't found any clues about the forbidden tomes. It's turning into a real headache for me.
::'''Yuluo:''' Oh, by your astonished expression, I can tell that you actually want to say "Come on! Has the Alchemy Commission ever done anything right!?" Well, now you see how perilous my position as the chief alchemist is.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_404025001_23-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_404025001_23-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why is the Alchemy Commission keeping those forbidden tomes?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414250011-->
:::'''Yuluo:''' Because these tomes are also medical texts &mdash; in a sense, they themselves are a treatment method. Just by reading them, patients will experience miraculous things.
:::'''Yuluo:''' For example, some patients who read the "Cure for Insomnia" fall asleep for a long time, while others who read "Fight Sleepiness" never fall asleep again...
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Aren't they super dangerous?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414250014-->
::::'''Yuluo:''' As long as you don't understand their contents, they should be safe.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_414250020-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414250020-->
::::'''Yuluo:''' There is a certain "reading barrier" for those forbidden tomes, so they are completely harmless to the majority of people.
::::'''Yuluo:''' However, if they fall into the hands of someone who is skilled at deciphering them... it pains me to imagine the terrible things that could happen. They must be retrieved as soon as possible.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You should destroy such dangerous books before it's too late...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414250016-->
::::'''Yuluo:''' Some healers in the Alchemy Commission also advocate for the destruction of the forbidden tomes just like you... but in my opinion, since those tomes have medicinal value, they can be really helpful if they end up in the right hands.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_414250020-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_414250020-->
